By combining knowledgeable staff with hyper-aggressive, targeted marketing, we are able to find buyers who are willing and able to pay top dollar for your used assets. Perfection welcomes the opportunity to review your specific requirements and goals. Description: NCDCR is the state agency with a vision to be the leader in using the state's cultural resources
Headquarters Regions: Research Triangle, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: The N.C. Department of Cultural Resources (NCDCR) is the state agency with a vision to be the leader in using the state's cultural resources to build the social, cultural and economic future of North Carolina. Led by Secretary Susan W. Kluttz, NCDCR's mission is to enrich lives and communities creates opportunities to experience excellence in the arts, history and libraries in North Carolina that will spark creativity, stimulate learning, preserve the state's history and promote the creative economy. NCDCR was the first state organization in the nation to include all agencies for arts and culture under one umbrella. Through arts efforts led by the N.C. Arts Council, the N.C. Symphony and the N.C. Museum of Art; NCDCR offers the opportunity for enriching arts education for young and old alike and economic stimulus engines for their state's communities. NCDCR's Divisions of State Archives, Historical Resources, State Historic Sites and State History Museums preserve, document and interpret North Carolina's rich cultural heritage. NCDCR's State Library of North Carolina is the principal library of state government and builds the capacity of all libraries in their state; developing and supporting access to traditional and online collections such as genealogy and resources for the blind and physically handicapped. NCDCR annually serves more than 19 million people through its 27 historic sites, seven history museums, two art museums, the nation's first state-supported Symphony Orchestra, the State Library, the N.C. Arts Council and the State Archives. NCDCR champions their state's creative industry that accounts for more than 300,000 jobs and generates nearly $18.5 billion in revenues. For more information, please call (919) 807-7300.

The R Consortium, Inc. is a group of businesses organized
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: The R Consortium, Inc. is a group of businesses organized under an open source governance and foundation model to provide support to the R community, the R Foundation and groups and individuals, using, maintaining and distributing R software. The R language is an open source environment for statistical computing and graphics, and runs on a wide variety of computing platforms. The R language has enjoyed significant growth, and now supports over 2 million users. A broad range of industries have adopted the R language, including biotech, finance, research and high technology industries. The R language is often integrated into third party analysis, visualization and reporting applications. The central mission of the R Consortium is to work with and provide support to the R Foundation and to the key organizations developing, maintaining, distributing and using R software through the identification, development and implementation of infrastructure projects. From a governance perspective, the business of the consortium is managed by a Board of Directors. The technical aspects of the project, including the development and implementation of infrastructure projects, is overseen by an Infrastructure Steering Committee. While the initial members of the Infrastructure Steering Committee consist of representatives of the founding members of the R Consortium, Inc., project leads of key infrastructure projects will become voting members of the Infrastructure Steering Committee.
Industry Groups: Hardware, Information Technology, Science and Engineering, Software

Full Description: Wakonda Technologies was founded in 2005 by Dr. Les Fritzemeier and Professor Ryne Raffaelle of the Rochester Institute of Technology. The company was established to exploit the intersection of their respective skills in metallurgical processing and advanced photovoltaic devices.  Wakonda was started in Rochester NY and used the facilities at RIT, Cornell University and several government agencies to conduct proof of concept experiments. In 2008, the company moved to Massachusetts to accelerate product development and early commercialization. Wakonda has received several honors over its short history, winning the first ever Golden Horseshoe Business Challenge in upstate NY and being named the National Renewable Energy Laboratory's Entrepreneur of the Year in 2007.

Full Description: StockLeap, LLC provides in-line tools for online news publishers/syndicates. Description: SilverFirst Inc is setting the pace in business consulting in New Orleans, LA and in the southeastern United States.
Full Description: SilverFirst Inc in Metairie welcomes you to our Crunchbase profile. If you've stumbled upon this page, it likely means that you've already read through our website, checked our our LinkedIn, Facebook, and all of our other social sites! We've decided to dedicate this space to sharing a little bit about what makes our New Orleans firm unique. We're not referring to our marketing campaigns; we're actually referring to the attributes and values that fuel the ongoing success in our work. Here are 10 behaviors we value at SilverFirst Inc: 1) First is integrity. This is the foundation for all that we do at SilverFirst Inc. We believe that results count for nothing if they're not earned honestly. We take pride in what we do. We wholeheartedly believe that being genuine and honest is always the answer. 2) Providing opportunity for our people. Working with the best comes with an important responsibility. We are the first to recognize the difference between a job and a career: a job is a short-term fix to put cash in your pocket, and a career is a long-term plan about which you're excited. We believe in nurturing and developing the talents of our team and providing them with career options worth getting excited about.  3) Cultivating a work environment that provides daily enrichment and learning. Other than a fast track to management, the biggest perk of our management training program at SilverFirst Inc is the hands-on learning. Our trainees are challenged each and every day. They are given new responsibilities on a weekly, even daily, basis. We hate stagnation and we strive for our people to always feel like they're growing. 4) Rewarding hard work. We offer advancement to those who earn it. Bonuses are fun too! We believe that positive reinforcement is one of the best ways to motivate our people. We love to spoil our team from time to time -- but first they have to earn it! The words "merit based" mean everything to us. 5) Operating as a team. Or one big family, you could say. Our mentality in Metairie is centered around a "people helping people" philosophy. We believe that having each other's backs is the only way to win. We believe that in helping others, we also help ourselves. While we're individually competitive, our focus is on the success of the team. 6) Leading by example. No one moves up at SilverFirst Inc without first mastering the position(s) below him or her. There's an important reason for this! The leaders at our firm will never ask their team members to do anything they haven't already done, or wouldn't be willing to do themselves. If that alone doesn't make us unique, we don't know what does!  7) Investing time in relationships. We said it already: SilverFirst Inc is a family. We got that way by spending quality time with one another, learning about histories, motivations, families, and more. We all get together after work on a weekly basis. We blur the lines of "work life" and "personal life" and it happens to be awesome. 8) Doing what it takes to get the job done. We do not believe in excuses. We believe in taking accountability for both the good and the bad results. We encourage our team members to think like business owners: "What would you do if this was 100% your responsibility and the only options were to sink or swim?"... that kind of thing! 9) Having a positive attitude. It's all about the glass being half full. Bad things happen to everyone, even our team members. But we choose to rise above whatever negative circumstances we might be handed on a given day, week, month, or year. At SilverFirst Inc we're always looking forward. This is one of the major keys to our success. 10) Having fun and enjoying the ride. No one ever said that you can't have a blast while you're on the ride to the top. Not only do we have tons of fun at the office and after work, but we travel together, meet cool people, and do fun things.
Industry Groups: Other, Professional Services, Sales and Marketing
